# Navigation Rules

See full spec: `docs/navigation-rules.md`

## Stack: React Navigation v7 (NOT Expo Router)

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT imports
import { useNavigation, useRoute } from '@react-navigation/native';
import { createNativeStackNavigator } from '@react-navigation/native-stack';

// ❌ BANNED — this project does not use Expo Router
import { useRouter } from 'expo-router';
```

## Typed Navigation — Mandatory

```typescript
// src/navigation/types.ts — ALL param lists live here
export type AppStackParamList = {
  Dashboard: undefined;
  ClientDetail: { clientId: string; clientName: string };
  ConsultancyDetail: { consultancyId: string };
};

// In screens — always typed
const navigation = useNavigation<NativeStackNavigationProp<AppStackParamList>>();
const route = useRoute<RouteProp<AppStackParamList, 'ClientDetail'>>();
```

## Navigator Setup

```typescript
const Stack = createNativeStackNavigator<AppStackParamList>();

// Default screen options for consistency
const defaultOptions: NativeStackNavigationOptions = {
  headerBackTitleVisible: false,
  headerTitleAlign: 'center',
  headerShadowVisible: false,
  animation: 'slide_from_right',
};
```

## Navigation Calls

```typescript
// navigate — go to screen (won't duplicate if already in stack)
navigation.navigate('ClientDetail', { clientId: '123', clientName: 'Acme' });

// push — always add new instance
navigation.push('ClientDetail', { clientId: '456', clientName: 'Beta' });

// replace — swap current (after login)
navigation.replace('Dashboard');

// reset — full stack reset (logout)
navigation.reset({ index: 0, routes: [{ name: 'Login' }] });
```

## Route Params — Serialisable Only

```typescript
// ✅ Pass primitives only
navigation.navigate('ClientDetail', { clientId: '123', clientName: 'Acme' });

// ❌ Never pass full objects — breaks deep links & serialisation
navigation.navigate('ClientDetail', { client: clientObject });
```

## Back Behaviour

- Back must be predictable — use `goBack()` for normal back flows
- Never reset stack silently mid-flow
- Preserve scroll position and filter state on back
- Never disable `gestureEnabled` (iOS swipe-back)

## Bottom Tabs

- Maximum **5 tab items**
- Every item: icon + text label (no icon-only)
- Bottom nav = top-level screens only — no nested sub-navigation inside tabs
- Apply safe area insets to `tabBarStyle`

## Modals

```typescript
// Use 'modal' presentation for sheets
<Stack.Screen
  name="CreateClient"
  component={CreateClientScreen}
  options={{ presentation: 'modal' }}
/>
```

- Always provide visible close/dismiss affordance
- Never use modals for primary navigation flows
- Confirm before dismissing with unsaved changes

## Deep Linking

- Every key screen must have a deep link path registered in `NavigationContainer`
- Prefix: `bizconsultancy://`

## Anti-Patterns

- ❌ `import from 'expo-router'`
- ❌ Untyped `useNavigation()` / `useRoute()`
- ❌ Passing objects as route params
- ❌ More than 5 bottom tab items
- ❌ Icon-only tab items
- ❌ Disabling swipe-back gesture
- ❌ Silently resetting navigation stack mid-flow
- ❌ Modals used for primary navigation screens
